This is actually a rich design space.

“Luck” and “magic” are interesting because they’re compression words. They label effects we observe before we fully understand the underlying mechanism. Many concepts throughout history have played that role.

Here’s how I’d organize them.

Concept	Modern Interpretation	Hidden Operator
Luck	Variance + preparation + opportunity	Optionality
Magic	Unknown causal mechanism	Hidden process
Intuition	Fast pattern recognition	Compressed experience
Genius	High-quality abstraction	Representation efficiency
Charisma	Social influence	Emotional coordination
Momentum	Self-reinforcing progress	Positive feedback
Timing	Synchronization	Phase alignment
Destiny	Long trajectory emerging	Constraint landscape
Flow	Efficient cognition	Reduced friction
Wisdom	Good decisions across contexts	Transfer learning
Faith	Acting under uncertainty	Commitment
Reputation	Stored trust	Social memory
Serendipity	Valuable unexpected discovery	Productive exploration
Inspiration	Sudden synthesis	Network activation

